observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:
Supply Officer and the Municipal Accountant to (i) reconcile the discrepancy between the book balance and the physical count report of the Office Supplies Inventory account, and (ii) make the necessary adjusting entries in their respective records;
Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical count of inventories for the first and second semesters and prepare the report to be submitted to the Audit Team not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year, respectively;
Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the disbursement voucher for the purchase of 45,000 sacks of rice worth ₱90 million together with the supporting documents; and
Supply Office and the Accounting Office to maintain SC and SLC, respectively, for each type of supply to record all receipts and issuances.

We recommended and Municipal Mayor agreed to instruct the:
Municipal Accountant to submit the related RIS, SSMI and other documents to support the Medical, Dental and Laboratory Supplies Expense (5020-3080) amounting to ₱15,739,061.05 for the year ended December 31, 2021.
Concerned personnel to follow the general process in the control of inventory as prescribed in Section 122, Chapter 7 of the NGAS Manual Volume I;
Municipal Accountant to course through the regular purchases of inventories to the inventory account and record the issuances thereof as they take place;
Municipal Accountant to record expenditures for the issued inventories based on the SSMI supported with the related RIS; and
This was communicated to Management through AOM No. 2022-019(2019-2021) dated June 3, 2022.

We recommended that Management submit the:
request/s by the End-User to the BAC or the HoPE identifying the emergency sought to be addressed, and the necessary goods that must be procured to address the emergency;
revised and approved Annual Procurement Plan showing the subject purchases and their procurement method used;
justification on the deficiencies noted on the (i) Purchase Orders, (ii) Requisition and Issue Slips, (iii) Acceptance and Inspection Reports and (iv) the BAC Recommendation and Award resolutions; and
information on the estimates as to the number of meals prepared for the ingredients/raw materials purchased and the recipients thereof.
